Today, we are going to learn about recycling!
Recycling is when certain items can be used and transformed into something brand new!
There are 3 main categories: paper, glass, and plastic.

Things that can go into the plastic can are soap bottles, styrofoam, yogurt containers, etc.

Reusability is when the same item can be used multiple times for various purposes.
For example, a plastic water bottle can only be used once.
But a metal water bottle can be used many times, and can hold different liquids such as coffee, juice, tea, and water.

Hi, my name is Meghana, and I am going to teach you about composting!
Composting is when you can put used things back into the environment, and they will degrade over time.
It is usually done with plant-based items and food products, like popsicle sticks and banana peels.
But, dairy products and meat cannot be composted.
